{
  "texts": [
    "Combining SF with other materials like MK or steel fibers also provided notable benefits.",
    "Sankarp and Ramadoss [50] reported increases in compressive and flexural strengths of 29.7% and 37.8%, respectively, with SF and MK.",
    "Liu et al. [51] found similar gains when SF was combined with steel fibers.",
    "FAIncorporating FA in concrete initially reduces compressive strength, but strength can improve over time.",
    "Sadrmomtazi et al. [42] noted a 20% decrease in compressive strength and a 15% reduction in flexural strength with a 30% FA replacement due to micro-cracks, while at a 40% replacement level, compressive strength initially decreased by 18% but showed significant gains after 28 days these findings investigated by saha et al."
  ]
